        "answer": "In a custodial wallet, the business holds the private keys on behalf of users. Users cannot access their funds without the business's cooperation. In a non-custodial wallet, users hold their own private keys and are solely responsible for their security. Custodial wallets provide a better user experience (no seed phrase to manage) but require the business to implement institutional-grade security and comply with custody regulations. [→ Read the full comparison](/custodial-vs-non-custodial-wallet/)"
