        "question": "Can we extend vesting if the market is bad?",
        "answer": "If the vesting contract is revocable by the owner: yes, technically. But retroactively extending investor vesting can create legal disputes (investors agreed to a specific schedule). Team vesting extension can be framed as commitment — if done publicly and proactively (not in response to a price crash), it can actually be positive signal. Consult legal counsel before any vesting modification."
