        "question": "Which order types are required at minimum for a production exchange?",
        "answer": "Minimum viable exchange: Limit (GTC and IOC) + Market. These cover 90%+ of retail trading volume. Stop-Limit adds risk management capability for most retail traders. OCO, TWAP, and Iceberg orders are institutional requirements that can be added in phase 2."
