        "heading": "Why Supply Chain Blockchain Works",
        "content": "Supply chain has the classic multi-party trust problem blockchain is designed to solve. A pharmaceutical distributor, their 22 suppliers, and their 340 pharmacy customers all have conflicting data about the same shipments. Every reconciliation dispute costs $800 and 4 hours.\n\nOn a shared blockchain: each custody event is recorded once by the party who created it. Disputes are mathematically eliminated — there is only one record, and all parties can see it.\n\n---"
