        "question": "What is a dApp and how is it different from a regular app?",
        "answer": "A decentralized application (dApp) has some or all of its logic running on a blockchain rather than on centralized servers. The primary implication is that the logic is transparent, auditable, and cannot be altered after deployment without a governance process. For users, this means they can verify the application is operating as stated — a property that no Web2 application can offer. [→ Read our full Web3 explainer](/what-is-web3/)"
